cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper discusses the resource allocation issues in D2D communication, which is a subfield of wireless networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also extensively uses game theory to model and analyze the behavior of D2D users, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also mentions the use of mathematical tools to model and analyze D2D communication, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the possibility of using game models to provide distributed solutions to resource allocation problems, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of D2D communication in multimedia transmission, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
